Reasoning: The paper discusses congestion control and traffic management in ATM networks, which are topics related to computer networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses security issues related to congestion control, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses the selection criteria for congestion control mechanisms, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the different approaches to congestion control, which could fall under cs.COM (Computers and Society) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
